Spotted it on strip-mall-lane while hunting for tucker, and it absolutely hit the spot.
I'm not a great pho fan, because I don't like all the liquid, so got the most expensive thing on the menu (at $10.50) ,  the "combination with crispy egg noodles" and was delighted.
Although crispy noodles can be plain and crunchy, these were thin  and fine enough to slowly melt into the "special sauce" , pleasantly changing the texture of the meal over time - - but the real joy was the range of seafood, mushroom, veggie, and pork slices that turned it into a delicate feast.
In particular, the slabs of pork were incredibly savory and succulent - - something you don't expect.
The meal was like a "best of" platter of asian delights and accents arrayed in pleasant variety, in sight and flavor.
A very satisfying, well conceived, and well prepared surprise.
Next time I go (and it will be soon) I'm trying the seafood vermicelli combination.

